question.text: Set your current location as inspection location using the pin below

question.title: Asset Accessibility
question.text: Ensure that: - Assets are in the assigned location - Assets readily accessible, e.g. free to open without obstruction (cabinet hose reels) - Assets are securely fitted - Signage is in place - Operating instructions are legible

question.title: Asset Tags
question.text: Ensure that the: - Fire extinguisher anti-tamper device is intact - Maintenance record (white stickers) are present and legible - Annual inspection tag is firmly attached and current

question.title: Asset Exterior
question.text:
Check that they are: - Clean - Free of corrosion or visual damage - Within operable range on the pressure indicator (fire extinguishers) - Not blocked or damaged, i.e. discharge nozzle, hoses - Free from cracking, damage or deterioration (hose reels) - Connected to supply and on (hose reels) - Pressurized (water supply), i.e. water flows through the reel and out of the nozzle, when the nozzle is opened, then closed and hose depressurized with the stop valve is turned off, (hose reels)
Note: Where hose reels are interconnected to a Sprinkler Fire Protection System testing of pressure is to be conducted by the Fire Protection System Tester.
